description: Quotient: squarefree kernel of LCM[1,..,n] (or of n!) divided by kernel of central binomial coefficient.
example: n = 10, LCM[1, 2, 3, .., 10] = 2520, LCM[1, 10, 45, 120, 210, 252] = 252; the corresponding kernels are 210 or 42. The quotient is a(10) = 5.
author: _Labos Elemer_, Aug 07 2000
